.SH NAME
circleci-migrate-secrets-merge - Merge multiple secret bundles into one.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate secrets merge -o  \&... [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
merge combines several secret bundles (for example, the per-context
bundles produced by separate extraction jobs) into a single bundle.

.PP
Example:
  circleci-migrate secrets merge -o secrets.json artifacts/*/secrets.json


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for merge

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="secrets.json"
	Path to write the merged bundle


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_HOST)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN)


